        "type": "text",
        "text": "Perfect! ✅ Circuit built successfully.\n\n### **Wiring Summary**\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Pin Role |\n|-------------|-----------|----------|\n| D2 | 7-seg A (via R_A) | Segment a |\n| D3 | 7-seg B (via R_B) | Segment b |\n| D4 | 7-seg C (via R_C) | Segment c |\n| D5 | 7-seg D (via R_D) | Segment d |\n| D6 | 7-seg E (via R_E) | Segment e |\n| D7 | 7-seg F (via R_F) | Segment f |\n| D8 | 7-seg G (via R_G) | Segment g |\n| D9 | BTN_INC (pin A) | Increment button |\n| D10 | BTN_DEC (pin A) | Decrement button |\n| GND | 7-seg GND, BTN pins B | Ground rail |\n\n### **How It Works**\n- **Increment button** (D9): Press to increase counter (0–9), clamps at 9.\n- **Decrement button** (D10): Press to decrease counter, clamps at 0.\n- **7-segment display**: Shows current digit with debouncing (20 ms delay).\n- **Segment control**: Each segment driven through a 220Ω resistor (~11 mA per LED segment at 5V).\n\n### **Power Budget**\n- **Per-pin load**: D2–D8 (segments): ~11 mA each (7 segments max = 77 mA).\n- **Button pins** (D9–D10): <1 mA (digital input).\n- **Total board draw**: ~80 mA (well within Arduino Uno 500 mA USB limit).\n- **Safety**: ✅ All pins ≤ 20 mA single constraint met; total is safe.\n\nYour counter is ready! Press the buttons to increment/decrement, and enjoy the 0–9 range with hard stops at the limits."
